    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_fasyn" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>fasyn</orth><form type="participle"
                            ><orth>fast</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>fasun</orth><form
                        type="participle"><orth>fast</orth></form></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>причесывать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>brush</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>расчесывать</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>comb (one's hair)</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>særvasæn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>гребень (для расчесывания)</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>comb</q>
                        </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из %især-fasæn%i) </note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from %især-fasæn%i) </note></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ḱyzg jæ særyq˳yntæ fasy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>девушка причесывает волосы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a girl is combing her hair</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Общеиндоевропейский глагол. Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pas-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*peḱ-</w></mentioned>. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>nuvāš-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                            (←%i*ni-pašš-%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                            (←%i*ni-pašš-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>причесывать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>na-pös-an, ni-pes, nə-bəs</w>
                        <gloss><q>гребень</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pašna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>веко</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pakšman-</w>
                        <gloss><q>ресница</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>peszù, pèszti</w>
                        <gloss><q>драть, трепать за волосы</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>fahs</w>
                        <gloss><q>волосы</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>πέκω</w>
                        <gloss><q>причесываю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>стригу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>ττέχος, πόχος</w>
                        <gloss><q>стриженая шерсть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>руно</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pecto</w>
                        <gloss><q>чешу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>причесываю</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pecten</w>
                        <gloss><q>гребень</q></gloss></mentioned>. От этого же корня происходит <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_fæsm"/> ‘шерсть осенней стрижки’, а также,
                    вероятно, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fys"/> (← %ipasu-%i) ‘овца’ (как
                    животное, дающее шерсть). На нулевой ступени огласовки корень %ipas-%i получал
                    вид %ips-%i → %ifš-%i, откуда, очевидно, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>šāna</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %ifšāna%i)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from %ifšāna%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>гребень</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>āfšūn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>šfīn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>š%rə%rfūn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/>
                        <w>šəfūn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>vešūj</w>
                        <gloss><q>гребень</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>168</biblScope></bibl>). Ср.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_særvasæn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ZDMG"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XLII
                            419 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XLII 419
                        ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">A general Indo-European word. It traces back to <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*pas-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/>
                        <w>*peḱ-</w></mentioned>. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>nuvāš-</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">
                            (←%i*ni-pašš-%i)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">
                            (←%i*ni-pašš-%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>comb (verb)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"><lang/>
                        <w>na-pös-an, ni-pes, nə-bəs</w>
                        <gloss><q>comb (noun)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>pašna-</w>
                        <gloss><q>eyelid</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>pakšman-</w>
                        <gloss><q>eyelash</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>peszù, pèszti</w>
                        <gloss><q>pull smb.'s hair</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>fahs</w>
                        <gloss><q>hair</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>πέκω</w>
                        <gloss><q>I am combing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>I am cutting</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                            ><w>ττέχος, πόχος</w>
                        <gloss><q>cut wool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>fleece</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pecto</w>
                        <gloss><q>I am scratching</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>I am combing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/>
                        <w>pecten</w>
                        <gloss><q>comb (noun)</q></gloss></mentioned>. The following words are from
                    the same root: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fæsm"/> ‘wool, cut in autumn’, and
                    probably also <ref type="xr" target="#entry_fys"/> (← %ipasu-%i) ‘sheep’ (as an
                    animal, which gives wool). At the zero ablaut grade the stem %ipas-%i looked
                    like %ips-%i → %ifš-%i, from which evidently are <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>šāna</w><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (из %ifšāna%i)</note><note
                            type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from %ifšāna%i)</note>
                        <gloss><q>comb (noun)</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"><lang/>
                        <w>āfšūn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"><lang/>
                        <w>šfīn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/>
                        <w>š%rə%rfūn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="isk"><lang/>
                        <w>šəfūn</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/>
                        <w>vešūj</w>
                        <gloss><q>comb (noun)</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Зарубин._Мундж."/><biblScope>168</biblScope></bibl>). Cf.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_særvasæn"/>.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl>. —
                            <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ZDMG"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">XLII
                            419 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">XLII 419
                        ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>24</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
